The slaty gnateater (Conopophaga ardesiaca) is a species of bird in the family Conopophagidae.
It is found in the Yungas of Bolivia and eastern Peru.
Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. The slaty gnateater has two sub-species:

C. a. saturata von Berlepsch & Stolzmann, 1906 - southeast Peru
C. a. ardesiaca D'Orbigny & Lafresnaye, 1837 - Bolivia and Peru